comments.body:
Do you guys think this compromises the security of the Tor project? By the look of it, it's tradecraft allright. When I see people endlessly arguing about the NSA planting a backdoor into Secp256r1 and say nothing about this, it makes me sick.

Is your trust in the project somewhat shaken?

Does it warrant a fork?

Should ZeroNet accelerate I2P support ?

What are you going to do about it?
